      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ABBOU (4) missed when leading last start at Pinjarra to just miss by 0.5L. This is much easier and he boasts a strong third-up record. He missed the placings in his only attempt at this track and trip, but there's plenty to like following his last start and he can get the job done this time around. WAYNE THE PAIN (2) has been narrowly beaten in his past couple, beaten 0.9L most recently at Albany. Yuill takes the ride today from a good draw and he can play a leading role stepping out to a more preferred distance. SNIP OF GOSSIP (5) settled well back last start and never threatened when 6 lengths from the winner in ninth over 1500m at York. Suitably placed so anticipating a better run this time.  PECOS (3) turned in another moderate effort last start when 7 lengths from the winner in 12th over 1800m at Ascot. Well placed to bounce back. MAGIC WHISTLE (1) is next.",
